Preconditions:
The input integer n represents the number of engineers in the team.
The input arrays speed and efficiency represent the speed and efficiency values of each engineer respectively.
The length of the arrays speed and efficiency is equal to n.
The input integer k represents the maximum number of engineers that can be selected for the team.
The value of n is greater than or equal to k.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the maximum performance of the team.
The returned value is the maximum performance modulo 10^9 + 7.